framework

Interface IImpact


  • public interface IImpact
    Interface implemented by objects that represent the impact of a projectile on a piece, or the projectile's exit from the playing area. Note: students do not need to create an implementation of this interface. All objects that implement it are created by the game engine.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getAngle

        double getAngle()
        Get the angle of incidence of the projectile
        Returns:
        angle of incidence in radians (calculated as angle between the direction of the incoming projectile and the tangent to the surface of the piece, at the point of impact).

      • getPiece

        IPiece getPiece()
        Get the piece (if any) on which the impact has occurred
        Returns:
        null if this object represents the projectile's exit from the playing area, otherwise a reference to the piece on which the impact occurred.

      • getProjectile

        IProjectile getProjectile()
        Get the projectile
        Returns:
        the projectile that caused the impact

      • getxImpact

        double getxImpact()
        Get the x coordinate of impact
        Returns:
        the x coordinate of the point at which the impact occurred, in game coordinates

      • getyImpact

        double getyImpact()
        Get the y coordinate of impact
        Returns:
        the x coordinate of the point at which the impact occurred, in game coordinates
